yingyinNormal.zh: 好吧，你有没有考虑过提高你的社交技能呢，好让你更有效地和别人交流？

yingyinNormal.en: Some regulate the cell cycle more effectively than others.
yingyinNormal.zh: 它们中的某些在调节细胞周期上比其他要更高效。

yingyinNormal.en: And unfortunately that effectively ends your relationship with him.
yingyinNormal.zh: 并且不幸的是，这样就要结束你和他的关系。

yingyinNormal.en: So on top of L-Dopa, they gave these kids a serotonin precursor drug, and they're effectively normal now.
yingyinNormal.zh: 所以除了L－多巴，他们也用血清素前体药物辅以治疗，孩子们恢复正常了。

yingyinNormal.en: That resulted in a tremendous surge of power. It overloaded our transmission lines and effectively caused the blackout in New York.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这引发了更恶劣的后果，其它高压线不堪负荷使纽约州整个电网陷入瘫痪。

yingyinNormal.en: If you saw them free of the distortions produced by your ego or your blind spots, you would be able to deal with them more effectively.
yingyinNormal.zh: 如果你能客观的看待他们不受自负和盲点的左右，就可以更高效的处理他们。

yingyinNormal.en: A staggering 50% of America's fruits and nuts are grown in California's central valley, what's effectively a giant, open-air food factory powered by the sun.
yingyinNormal.zh: 美国消费的一半的水果和坚果都产自加州中央山谷，那是一个巨大的露天工厂，驱动力就是太阳。

yingyinNormal.en: As four point night Penny blossoms per hour. Based on your cost materials and your wholesale selling price, you'll effectively be paying yourself $5.19 a day.
yingyinNormal.zh: 计算佩妮花花一小时的产量是4.9个，再算上批量购买的材料费用，你一天实际上只能赚... 5.19美元。

yingyinNormal.en: There were two types of vinyl in the burnt-out remains of the car. One, the actual passenger seat, the other, a good copy. Well, good enough. Effectively a costume.
yingyinNormal.zh: 在被烧毁的车的残骸中，发现了两种氯乙烯，一种是座椅上的，另一种是个仿品，仿得还挺像，相当于伪装。
